<paragraph id="8BFD36D586006B26FEC78B50FB03F8D0" blockId="18.[237,1222,1643,2143]" box="[287,1177,1828,1867]" pageId="18" pageNumber="81">Geographic distribution. 'Lorrina' to Glenbawn.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D586006B26FEC78B26FC1FF8E2" blockId="18.[237,1222,1643,2143]" box="[287,901,1874,1913]" pageId="18" pageNumber="81">Geological age. Late Tournaisian.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D586006B26FEC78BF5FBEFF7C4" blockId="18.[237,1222,1643,2143]" pageId="18" pageNumber="81">
Remarks. This species has a very thin shell, yet is extremely well preserved. It is one of the most abundant species at the 
<typeStatus id="54F9887786006B26FDDD8BA9FDD1F79F" box="[517,587,2013,2052]" pageId="18" pageNumber="81">type</typeStatus>
locality. A single worn specimen recovered from the upper part of the Namoi Formation at 'Lorrina' is tentatively referred to this species.
</paragraph>
